# MBA Design Rules - Core Principles

## Mission
Generate UI/UX that looks professionally designed by humans, not AI. Every design decision must be intentional, consistent, and grounded in established design systems.

## Reference Design Systems
Always reference patterns from:
- **Adobe Spectrum**: `.mba-template/design-systems/adobe-spectrum/`
- **IBM Carbon**: `.mba-template/design-systems/ibm-carbon/`
- **Material Design 3**: `.mba-template/design-systems/material-design-3/`
- **Apple HIG**: `.mba-template/design-systems/apple-hig/`
- **Microsoft Fluent 2**: `.mba-template/design-systems/microsoft-fluent-2/`

## Core Principles

### 1. Content-First Hierarchy
- **Clear heading structure**: H1 > H2 > H3 (size, weight, spacing)
- **Supporting text**: Secondary information uses lighter weight or smaller size
- **Primary action**: Most prominent button (filled, brand color)
- **Secondary actions**: Less prominent (outlined, ghost)
- **Tertiary actions**: Minimal emphasis (text-only links)

### 2. Consistent Spacing System
**NEVER use random pixel values.**

Choose ONE base unit system:
- **4px base**: 4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64 (Material Design, Fluent)
- **8px base**: 8, 16, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64, 96 (Spectrum)
- **2px base**: 2, 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48 (Carbon - for dense UIs)

Apply consistently:
- Component padding: Use scale values
- Margins between elements: Use scale values
- Section spacing: Larger scale values (32px, 48px, 64px)

### 3. Limited, Purposeful Color Palette
**NEVER use rainbow colors without semantic meaning.**

Color roles:
- **Primary**: Brand color (1 color)
- **Secondary**: Complementary accent (optional, 1 color)
- **Success**: Green (#10B981, #34C759, #24a148)
- **Warning**: Orange/Yellow (#F59E0B, #FF9500, #f1c21b)
- **Error**: Red (#EF4444, #FF3B30, #da1e28)
- **Neutral**: Grays (6-10 shades from white to black)

### 4. Semantic HTML Structure
**ALWAYS use proper semantic elements.**

Required landmarks:
- `<header>`: Page/section header
- `<nav>`: Navigation menus
- `<main>`: Primary content (one per page)
- `<section>`: Thematic grouping
- `<article>`: Self-contained content
- `<aside>`: Tangential content
- `<footer>`: Page/section footer

Avoid:
- `<div>` soup (divs everywhere without semantic meaning)
- Missing heading hierarchy
- Non-semantic button elements (`<div onclick>`)

### 5. Real, Purposeful Content
**NEVER use Lorem Ipsum or generic placeholders.**

Instead use:
- **Company names**: Realistic tech/business names (e.g., "Acme Analytics", "Vertex Systems")
- **Product names**: Descriptive, believable (e.g., "Enterprise Dashboard Pro", "CloudSync")
- **Headlines**: Concise, under 60 characters
- **Body text**: 2-3 sentences, relevant to context
- **Data**: Realistic numbers with appropriate formatting ($1,234.56, 45.2%, 1,234 users)
- **Dates**: Varied, recent dates (not all same day)
- **Names**: Diverse, realistic names (not just "John Doe")

### 6. Appropriate Border Radius
**NEVER over-round corners.**

Guidelines:
- **Small elements** (buttons, inputs, tags): 4-8px
- **Medium elements** (cards, modals): 8-12px
- **Large elements** (sections, panels): 12-16px
- **Maximum**: 16px (except pills/avatars which can be fully rounded)

Consistency:
- Use 2-3 radius values maximum across entire interface
- Same element type = same radius

### 7. Accessibility First
**ALWAYS meet WCAG AA standards minimum.**

Requirements:
- **Text contrast**: 4.5:1 minimum (body text), 3:1 (large text 18px+)
- **Touch targets**: 44px × 44px minimum (mobile/touch), 32px × 32px (desktop)
- **Focus indicators**: 2px outline, sufficient contrast, visible on all interactive elements
- **Keyboard navigation**: All features accessible via keyboard
- **ARIA labels**: Meaningful labels for screen readers
- **Alt text**: Descriptive alt text for images
- **Form labels**: Every input has associated label

### 8. Platform-Appropriate Patterns
**ALWAYS respect platform conventions.**

- **Web**: Reference `.mba-template/platforms/web-responsive.md`
- **Desktop**: Reference `.mba-template/platforms/desktop-apps.md`
- **iOS**: Reference `.mba-template/platforms/ios-mobile.md`
- **Android**: Reference `.mba-template/platforms/android-mobile.md`

### 9. Avoid AI-Generated Tells
**ALWAYS review** `.mba-template/anti-patterns/ai-generated-tells.md`

Common mistakes to avoid:
- Excessive gradients everywhere
- Random spacing values (7px, 13px, 19px)
- Over-rounded corners (>16px on small elements)
- Low contrast text
- Generic placeholder text
- Rainbow colors without purpose
- Centered-everything layouts
- Inconsistent component sizing

### 10. Design System Consistency
**ALWAYS maintain internal consistency.**

Within a single project:
- Same button styles throughout
- Same color roles (blue always means primary, red always means error)
- Same spacing scale
- Same typography scale
- Same border radius values
- Same shadow/elevation system

## Decision Framework

When making any design decision, ask:
1. **Is this consistent** with the spacing/color/typography system?
2. **Is this accessible** (contrast, touch targets, keyboard nav)?
3. **Is this semantic** (proper HTML elements, ARIA)?
4. **Is this realistic** (real content, not placeholders)?
5. **Is this professional** (would a human designer do this)?

## Quality Checklist

Before finalizing any design:
- [ ] Spacing uses consistent scale (no random px values)
- [ ] Colors have semantic meaning
- [ ] Typography follows clear hierarchy
- [ ] Semantic HTML structure
- [ ] Real, purposeful content
- [ ] WCAG AA contrast ratios
- [ ] Touch targets meet minimum sizes
- [ ] Focus states visible
- [ ] Border radius consistent (2-3 values max)
- [ ] No obvious AI-generated tells
- [ ] Platform-appropriate patterns
- [ ] Internal consistency maintained

